<br>
I have always dual boxed My Wizard with my warrior Main in a group environment. Now that My wizzy is level 60, I have been working on getting him run3 and I am thinking it would be fun to try him solo for a much needed change of Pace.<br>
The question is this: How on earth do i solo &quot;quad&quot; Kite and where is the best place to do this?<br>
I tried soloing in Maiden's Eye on Umbrous Toilers and used my AE snare and found a few that resisted and I ended up running my arse off and could never get far enough away that I could cast my spell without getting raped. Basically I found the time spent trying to Kite in ME was wasted by the number of times I died and I dont want to be asking for rezzes every 30 minutes.<br>
<br>
Any tips will be appreciated.<br>
<br>
Phourphoot PhizzlePhingers<br>
60 Wizard of VoLS<br>
the Rathe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laeyakk>Laeyakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/03 11:59 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 60 n00b asks: How do I solo Kite?</span><hr size=1> Get SoW and/or jboots and/or RS3 and/or a fast horse in order to kite.  SoW potions are cheap.  Jboots aren't much more expensive.<br>
<br>
Run a long way, pausing in an area with good LoS, and snare the group of unsnared folk running after you.<br>
<br>
Once all 4 mobs are snared, run in as tight a circle around them as you can in order to group them up.<br>
<br>
Once they are tightly grouped, use pillar nukes to toast all 4 at once.  If you can't hit all 4 at once, you didn't group them tight enough.<br>
<br>
It might be a good idea to practice &quot;grouping&quot; mobs with greens. Go to EW, and pull 4 of 1 kind of mob with your tstaff, keeping them spread out.  Now, snare them all and group them up tight, and blast'm.  Just for practice.<br>
<br>
Another useful idea is to try &quot;quadding&quot; 2 mobs at a time for practice.  Less things can go wrong, and it is less fatal, when you only have 2 mobs following you.<br>
<br>
To test/practice your mana pool/casting range/get LoS practice, some wizards even &quot;quad&quot; 1 mob at a time.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=malakriss>Malakriss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 285<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/03 12:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 60 n00b asks: How do I solo Kite?</span><hr size=1> Luclin line of sight basically sucks ass.  The way they did zone geometry in Luclin basically makes it so every hill and nook counts as a &quot;wall&quot; like an indoor zone and if you can't see a whole mob it won't let you cast.  Same reason why you can't warp eyes.  Stay out in the middle open areas so you don't have worry about that, always have a root + snare memmed, and sow potions are a very good idea.  Also third person view can help a lot with checking distance and avoiding adds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/03 12:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 60 n00b asks: How do I solo Kite?</span><hr size=1> If you worry bout adds go to pod and do flies (there is a map someware showing very detailed paths) there you can get the hang of quadding, very eazy spot. One thing tho, what lucilin was laking in LoS, PoP is laking in pathing, dont go over the water is the rumor hehe.<br>
<br>
 At 60 you should really not get almost any resists on atols, and if you have epic the &quot;add&quot; is just a nuisance while you root snare, if you dont have epic you can use the runes that cost 1 peridot or if your fealing lucky steelskin for a jasper. The exp is amazing once you get past the learning curve.<br>
<br>
F3 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tigertailz>tigertailz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 522<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/03 4:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 60 n00b asks: How do I solo Kite?</span><hr size=1> just use your flux staff (you have this RIGHT?!?) to pull 4 mobs run in circles to group them....then run in a straight line while spamming your flux staff. once you get out of range message stop running forward and spin 90degrees one way then cast snare....any that resist spin them around and repeat....get them all bunched and resnare...then just nuke em down and enjoy the pretty yellow messages <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Piaoliang Fengbao - Wizard 65 - Karana<br>
