Ayonae Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kyron>Kyron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 314<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/03 5:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 60 n00b asks: How do I solo Kite?</span><hr size=1> Go to Iceclad Ocean and practice quading on the giants near the bridge. The area is WIDE OPEN and very easy to learn quading in. The mobs won't give you exp, but you will not die while you are refining your skills. Once you can pull 4, round them up, snare, and nuke them down, you can move to ME for actual exp.<br>
<br>
You will have to learn to deal with mobs that resist the snare of the first cast. Its not really a big deal, just do it a while and you will see.<br>
<br>
You don't need Ext Range items to quad, just get a mage summoned ring, earring, and bracer and some C3 (last longer then C4-5) and have fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/03 8:27 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 60 n00b asks: How do I solo Kite?</span><hr size=1> When I started ME I was an experienced quader... However I hadn't done it since level 58 and I had gotten 18aa in that time too... I died like 5 times learning it. It sucked but I got alot of AA there to make up for it.<br>
<br>
The &quot;pit&quot; looking around is a good place to sit and med. I rarely ever casted invis. The hardest part about quadding is learning where the spawns are and the pathing lanes and pulling. Make up your own style too and make sure you can adjust it in case a toiler pops in your path. I suggest getting a 2.5 minute timer built into your UI... Not sure what the link is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ziggie204>ziggie204</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/03 11:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 60 n00b asks: How do I solo Kite?</span><hr size=1> Weird, I have been living off toilers for 2 levels and 8 aa now and I dont remember a single atols resist in that time.<br>
<br>
And yes, with a rune up adds are trivial, just snare/root and finish off the other 4.  After that, if you have decent mana regen, just keep it fettered until you have enough to do another quad.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.bound-by-honor.com/images/upload/members/ziggiesig2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ziggie204>ziggie204</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/03 11:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 60 n00b asks: How do I solo Kite?</span><hr size=1> Oh and use sow potions.  I have a pair of jboots in the bag, but I would rather just use the extra speed of sow.  You kill quicker, but it costs you more to do it.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.bound-by-honor.com/images/upload/members/ziggiesig2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daeanorendarion>Daeanor Endarion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1017<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/03 7:04 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 60 n00b asks: How do I solo Kite?</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't consider a fast horse a prerequisite for quadding at all. I did all of levels 58-60 and my first 12 AA before I got a horse. The stop-start time is too much for me when quadding with a horse. I didn't even get sow, jboots, then run3 when I got it, were adequate for most situations. Personally, I quadded in the Grey. Once you get the hang of dealing with rockfiends, it's rather easy there I thought, especially the nice, slow golems.<br>
<br>
But I agree with a previous poster - learn to do it with greens. Practice rounding them up, the timing of your pillars, all that stuff, with mobs that won't slaughter you in ten seconds if you make a mistake. Then, when you are more confident, go &quot;live&quot; with it. <p><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">function stat_on(){self.status="Click for Magelo profile"}</script><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">function stat_off(){self.status=""}</script><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">function show_url(url_txt){newWindow = window.open("http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=" + url_txt)}</script><table><tr><td colspan = 2 align="center" style="filter:glow(color=#cc0000); cursor:hand" onClick=show_url("23437") onMouseover=stat_on() OnMouseOut=stat_off()  strength="1"><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</font></td></tr>
