<br>
One more tip on quadding, Once you get the grouping done and killed your first quads, do the following:<br>
<br>
Load up on Bonds of Force (Not Atols)<br>
Load up Circle of Force (or another pre 50 AE quad spell) <br>
<br>
And now quad again. This way you learn what it means to resnare during a quad when your quad takes longer then 2.5 minutes to kill. <br>
<br>
For the real fun, pull 8 instead of 4 mobs and do them both, this is how Toilers will end up being the first time. If you have adds, add them to your quad and keep them snared while you kill off your first batch. The cast Abscond or finish a second group of 4. <br>
<br>
Although, at 60, you might want to start quadding Trap mobs, more hp but also better xp then toilers.  <p><center>
