<br>
It has the distinction of having almost exactly the same range as our spells.  <br>
<br>
After you aggro all 4 and get them nice and tightly packed, you run straight.  All the while, spam click the Staff. You dont care if they resist or not.  The idea is to check your range...to see how far away you are.<br>
<br>
Once you see 5-6 Out of Range messages, stop.  Pause a second, then cast Snare.  Then run, doing the spam thing again until you get 3-4 Out of Range messages.  Stop. Pause a second. Then cast Pillar of Flame.<br>
<br>
This way, you know exactly how much time you have before they get too close to you.  It is absolutely invaluable, I have heard wizards say they would give up their epic before their flux staff...I wouldn't...but some would <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
BTW, the pause a second is just to stop interrupts due to moving.  It takes the computer a second to catch up with the fact that you have stopped. Not a whole lot of things more annoying than stopping to cast and getting interrupts.<br>
<br>
